“Shaq Moore Day” ‼️ Growing up in Lauderhill/South Florida, all I wanted to do was play soccer and one day fulfill my dream of being a professional one day. But never would I have thought that one day I would be recognized in such a remarkable way from the place where it all started. Dec. 12th will officially be known as “Shaq Moore Day” in Lauderhill and couldn’t be more proud. Lauderhill, thank you for recognizing me and allowing me to inspire the next generation. To the kids and the community: Thank you for coming out and showing love, as I was you once. Don’t be afraid to dream because no dream is too big, the sky is the limit. One love🤘🏾 @cityoflauderhill

Found out more on our website in the link in bio.

Having been born and raised in South Florida, Lauderhill has always held a special place in my heart. So to celebrate my hometown recognizing December 12th, 2022 as “Shaq Moore Day”, through the @shaqmoorefoundation we present the first annual 💢Shaq Moore Day Clinic💢this Tuesday December 12th, 2023 at the Lauderhill Sports Complex from 5PM-7PM! Hope to see you there!

*Registration is FREE through the link in bio at the @shaqmoorefoundation IG Page!

*We will be giving away FREE shirts to those that attend!
HEAT CULTURE 🔥 Thank you for an amazing experience @miamiheat

WHAT A WEEKEND for the @shaqmoore Youth Classic this weekend in Trinidad and Tobago. The third annual edition of the event, which takes place every year in December, was held at Dwight Yorke Stadium in Bacolet, Tobago over the weekend. The small island, which is neighbor island to Trinidad but serves as one country, holds deep roots to Shaq Moore. The goal of the tournament is to offer a healthy competitive environment and exposure for teams across the Caribbean in return contribute to the overall development youth soccer in the Caribbean! 

Special acknowledgment to our sponsors and partners at Tobago Youth Football League @gatorade.tt 

@shaqmoorefoundation X  @shaqmooresoccer @tyfl_official = Shaq Moore Youth Classic 

Extremely greatful to Tobago Youth Football League for their hard work in developing youth football on the island! 

See you guys next year!

#ShaqMooreFoundation

Our 1st annual @shaqmoore Day Clinic was a great success! We celebrated with the city of Lauderhill’s honoring of Dec. 12th (Shaq Moore Day) with an evening full of fun, games, pictures, autographs and a lot more! Decked out in @shaqmoorefoundation shirts! 

Big thanks to all our sponsors especially @selectsportamerica and other partners who were able to make our first annual “Shaq Moore Day” Clinic a success! To all the players and families that came out for such a beautiful day together we appreciate you! And to the city of Lauderhill, FL we couldn’t do it without you! 

Looking forward to next year!
